00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
It's time for the final ingredient, combustion.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.000
Here, we're just looking at one-singled cell at a time. We're treating each cell on its own.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:13.000
We're not looking at the neighbors unlike as we did with diffusion and with winds.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:16.000
For this singled cell that we're currently looking at,

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.000
we have to take two different quantities into account.

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:24.000
The first is the temperature which we already know, it's measured in Kelvin.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
The second is the amount of woods that can be burned.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:34.000
Actually that should be something like a density of wood to be measured in kg/mÂ².

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:39.000
